  "local_port": 54442,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I apply driving license in Bangalore?",
  "response": "Applying for a driving license in Bangalore involves several steps. Below is a comprehensive guide to help you through the process:\n\n### 1. **Eligibility Criteria**\n   - You must be at least 18 years old for a private driving license.\n   - You should have completed a driving training course from a recognized institution (for certain vehicle types).\n   - You need to have a learner's license (valid for at least 30 days).\n\n### 2. **Documents Required**\n   - **Learner's License**: A copy of your learner's license.\n   - **Proof of Identity**: Aadhar card, passport, voter ID, etc.\n   - **Proof of Address**: Utility bill, bank statement, rental agreement, etc.\n   - **Age Proof**: Birth certificate, school leaving certificate, etc.\n   - **Passport-sized Photographs**: Usually 2-3 copies.\n   - **Form 1 (Medical Certificate)**: This may be required if you're above a certain age or if you have specific medical conditions.\n\n### 3. **Application Process**\n   - **Online Application**:\n     1. Visit the **Parivahan Sewa** website under the Ministry of Road Transport and Highways: [Parivahan Sewa](https://parivahan.gov.in/parivahan/).\n     2. Select \u2018Online Services\u2019 and choose \u2018Driving License Related Services\u2019.\n     3. Select your state (Karnataka) and then click on \u2018Apply for Driving License\u2019.\n     4. Fill in the required details and upload the necessary documents.\n     5. Pay the application fee online. The fee varies depending on the type of license and the vehicle category.\n\n   - **Offline Application**:\n     1. Visit the nearest Regional Transport Office (RTO) in Bangalore.\n     2. Obtain the application form (Form 4) or download it from the Parivahan Sewa website.\n     3. Fill in all the necessary details and submit it along with required documents and photographs.\n     4. Pay the required fee at the RTO counter.\n\n### 4. **Driving Test**\n   - After your application is submitted, you will be scheduled for a driving test at the RTO.\n   - Arrive at the RTO on the scheduled date with your learner's license and any other required documents.\n   - During the test, you'll be evaluated on your driving skills and adherence to traffic rules.\n\n### 5. **Receiving Your Driving License**\n   - If you pass the driving test, your application will be processed, and you will receive your driving license.\n   - You can either receive it via post or collect it from the RTO, depending on the options provided during your application.\n\n### 6. **Additional Information**\n   - Keep a close eye on the status of your application through the Parivahan Sewa website.\n   - Ensure that all documents are accurate and up-to-date to avoid any delays.\n\n### 7. **Contact Information**\n   - For any queries or assistance, you can contact the Karnataka Transport Department or visit your local RTO office.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to successfully apply for a driving license in Bangalore. Good luck!",
